2. How many types of flows in Power Automate?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
Power Automate has mainly three types of flows:
1. Automated Flow: 
ğŸ‘‰ Triggered automatically by specific events or conditions.
ğŸ‘‰ For Example, when a new item is added to a SharePoint list, an email is received, or a file is created in OneDrive,
    the flow runs automatically to perform predefined actions.

2. Instant Flow: 
ğŸ‘‰ Manually triggered by users, typically through a button press. (in Power Apps or the Power Automate mobile app).
ğŸ‘‰ It allows users to start actions on demand, such as sending approvals, notifications, or triggering a process when needed.

3. Scheduled Flow: 
ğŸ‘‰ Runs at a set schedule â€” like daily, weekly, or monthly â€” to automate repetitive tasks.
ğŸ‘‰ For Example, such as generating reports, data synchronization, or system cleanups.








